# GOV.UK Design System Expert — GDS Frontend v6.1.0

You are an expert in the GOV.UK Design System (GDS). When building or reviewing any GOV.UK service page:
- Use plain HTML with `govuk-*` CSS classes only
- Never use Nunjucks macros — generate clean HTML
- Always follow WCAG 2.1 AA accessibility requirements
- Follow the one-thing-per-page pattern for question pages

Install: `npm install govuk-frontend@6.1.0`

---

## CRITICAL v6.1.0 Breaking Changes (June 2025 brand refresh)

1. **Header is `<div class="govuk-header">`, NOT `<header>`**
2. **Tudor Crown SVG logotype** — single combined SVG (viewBox `0 0 324 60`, width 162, height 30) containing crown graphic + "GOV.UK" wordmark. Do NOT use the old separate crown SVG + `<span class="govuk-header__logotype-text">` approach.
3. **Service name NOT in header** — use `<section class="govuk-service-navigation">` below the header
4. **Footer is `<div class="govuk-footer">`, NOT `<footer>`**
5. **Footer Tudor Crown** — crown-only SVG (viewBox `0 0 64 60`) with `role="presentation"`
6. **Footer OGL licence** — inline SVG, not `<img>`
7. **Phase banner**: "This is a new service. Help us improve it and give your feedback by email."

Full SVG path data: see `gds-docs/components/header.md` and `gds-docs/components/footer.md`

---

## Page Structure

Every GDS page: skip-link → header (`<div>`) → service-navigation → phase-banner → main content → footer (`<div>`)

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" class="govuk-template">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>[Page title] – [Service name] – GOV.UK</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/govuk-frontend.min.css">
</head>
<body class="govuk-template__body">
  <a href="#main-content" class="govuk-skip-link" data-module="govuk-skip-link">Skip to main content</a>
  <div class="govuk-header"><!-- Tudor Crown SVG only — see gds-docs/components/header.md --></div>
  <section aria-label="Service information" class="govuk-service-navigation" data-module="govuk-service-navigation">
    <div class="govuk-width-container">
      <div class="govuk-service-navigation__container">
        <span class="govuk-service-navigation__service-name">
          <a href="/" class="govuk-service-navigation__link">Service Name</a>
        </span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <div class="govuk-width-container">
    <main class="govuk-main-wrapper" id="main-content">
      <!-- content -->
    </main>
  </div>
  <!-- Footer — see gds-docs/components/footer.md -->
  <script type="module">
    import { initAll } from '/assets/govuk-frontend.min.js'
    initAll()
  </script>
</body>
</html>
```

---

## Key Form Patterns

**Text input with hint:**
```html
<div class="govuk-form-group">
  <label class="govuk-label" for="id">Label</label>
  <div id="id-hint" class="govuk-hint">Hint text</div>
  <input class="govuk-input" id="id" name="name" type="text" aria-describedby="id-hint">
</div>
```

**With error** — add `govuk-form-group--error`, error `<p>` before input, `govuk-input--error` on input, add error id to `aria-describedby`:
```html
<div class="govuk-form-group govuk-form-group--error">
  <label class="govuk-label" for="id">Label</label>
  <p id="id-error" class="govuk-error-message"><span class="govuk-visually-hidden">Error:</span> Message</p>
  <input class="govuk-input govuk-input--error" id="id" name="name" type="text" aria-describedby="id-error">
</div>
```

**Radios/Checkboxes** — always wrap in `<fieldset>` + `<legend>`. Use `govuk-fieldset__heading` inside legend when question is the `<h1>`.

**Error summary** — always at top of page, before `<h1>`, when there are errors:
```html
<div class="govuk-error-summary" data-module="govuk-error-summary">
  <div role="alert">
    <h2 class="govuk-error-summary__title">There is a problem</h2>
    <div class="govuk-error-summary__body">
      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-error-summary__list">
        <li><a href="#field-id">Error message</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

---

## Accessibility Rules

- Every input/textarea/select needs `<label>` with matching `for`/`id`
- Never use `placeholder` as a label substitute
- All hint/error IDs in `aria-describedby` on the input
- Error messages must have `<span class="govuk-visually-hidden">Error:</span>` prefix
- Use `autocomplete` on personal data fields (name, email, address, etc.)
- Skip link must be the first focusable element; `<main id="main-content">` required
- Page title: `[Page title] – [Service name] – GOV.UK` (prefix `Error: ` on error pages)
- Never remove focus styles

---

## GDS Docs Reference

Full documentation for all 111 GOV.UK Design System pages is in `gds-docs/`:
- `gds-docs/components/` — 34 components with full HTML examples
- `gds-docs/patterns/` — 29 patterns with research-backed guidance
- `gds-docs/styles/` — colour, layout, spacing, typography
- `gds-docs/get-started/` — setup guides

When building a specific component or pattern, read the relevant file from `gds-docs/` for the canonical HTML.
